Pomodoro Timer
This Pomodoro Timer is a simple time management application designed to help improve focus and productivity. 
The app is based on the Pomodoro Technique, where you work for 25 minutes, take short breaks for 5 minutes, and after completing 4 work sessions, you take a longer break of 20 minutes.

How to Use
Start the Timer: Click the "Start" button to begin the first work session.
Work Sessions: You will be prompted to work for 25 minutes.
Short Breaks: After each work session, you will have a 5-minute short break.
Long Breaks: After completing 4 work sessions, a 20-minute long break will follow.
Reset Timer: Click the "Reset" button to stop the current session and reset the timer to the initial state.
The app keeps track of the number of work sessions completed and displays checkmarks (âœ”) to represent each session.

Features
Work Sessions: 25-minute focus periods.
Short Breaks: 5-minute breaks between work sessions.
Long Breaks: 20-minute breaks after completing 4 work sessions.
Reset Functionality: Allows you to reset the timer at any time.
Visual Countdown: Displays the countdown timer in a visual format using a tomato image.

Requirements
Python 3.x installed.
Tkinter: Tkinter is included with Python's standard library, so no additional installation is needed.
Math Module: The math module is part of Python's standard library.

Setup
Clone or download this repository to your local machine.
Ensure you have a file named tomato.png in the same directory as the script. This image will be used as part of the timer interface.
Running the Program
Open a terminal or command prompt.

Navigate to the directory where the script is located.

User Interface Elements
Start Button: Starts the countdown for the work session.
Reset Button: Resets the timer to its initial state.
Checkmark Display: A visual representation of completed work sessions.
Timer Label: Displays whether it's time to work, take a short break, or take a long break.
Enjoy using the Pomodoro Timer to boost your productivity!
